Sentencas: Pr0.4Sr0.6Co0.9-xFexNb0.1O3-delta (PSCFxN) (x = 0, 0.2, 0.4, 0.6 and 0.9) oxides are evaluated as symmetric electrode materials for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Effects of cobalt and iron proportions in Pr0.4Sr0.6Co0.9-xFexNb0.1O3-δ electrode material for symmetric solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Both the thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) and conductivity decrease with the increasing of Fe amount.
Titulo: Effects of cobalt and iron proportions in Pr0.4Sr0.6Co0.9-xFexNb0.1O3-δ electrode material for symmetric solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: With the increase in Fe content, more Fe4+ species are reduced to Fe3+, generating more oxygen vacancies.
Titulo: Effects of cobalt and iron proportions in Pr0.4Sr0.6Co0.9-xFexNb0.1O3-δ electrode material for symmetric solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It effectively promotes the oxygen incorporation kinetics, and lowers the polarization resistance (R-p).
Titulo: Effects of cobalt and iron proportions in Pr0.4Sr0.6Co0.9-xFexNb0.1O3-δ electrode material for symmetric solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: As a result, the PSCF0.6N exhibits the lowest polarization resistance of 0.028 and 0.077 Omega m(2) at 900 degrees C in air and hydrogen, respectively, and the highest electrical conductivity of 258.90 Scm(-1) at 650 degrees C among all the prepared PSCFxN materials.
Titulo: Effects of cobalt and iron proportions in Pr0.4Sr0.6Co0.9-xFexNb0.1O3-δ electrode material for symmetric solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Meanwhile, with the doping of Fe, the TEC decreases near to the electrolyte TEC value.
Titulo: Effects of cobalt and iron proportions in Pr0.4Sr0.6Co0.9-xFexNb0.1O3-δ electrode material for symmetric solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: As such, the peak power densities of the electrolyte supported PSCF0.6N-based symmetric SOFCs with different electrolyte thicknesses of 500, 400 and 300 mu m are 0.642, 0.713 and 0.891 Wcm(-2), respectively.
Titulo: Effects of cobalt and iron proportions in Pr0.4Sr0.6Co0.9-xFexNb0.1O3-δ electrode material for symmetric solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Meanwhile, the output voltage of the obtained PSCF0.6N/LSGM/PSCF0.6N symmetric SOFC decreases only 5% in 50 h stability test under a current density of 0.5 Acm(-2).
Titulo: Effects of cobalt and iron proportions in Pr0.4Sr0.6Co0.9-xFexNb0.1O3-δ electrode material for symmetric solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results indicate that the PSCF0.6N material should be a promising electrode material for the symmetric SOFCs.
Titulo: Effects of cobalt and iron proportions in Pr0.4Sr0.6Co0.9-xFexNb0.1O3-δ electrode material for symmetric solid oxide fuel cells
